# What is GUI tree
  * A GUI , or Graphical User Interface is any software that can allow the user to perform tasks through a graphical interface . 
  * Most GUI's are built off of some system or library that can only be used through the terminal or through programming, making it more user-friendly 
  <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64,">
# Some Examples of GUIs are 
  * Microsoft Windows Desktop .
  * Google Chrome .
  * Most Linux Distributions (Ubuntu, Debian) .
  * Almost all software and applications for any device has some sort of GUI .
--------------------------------------
# What is Source Tree 
  * SourceTree is a Git GUI allowing you to interact with your repositories through a graphical interface . 
  * it builds off of the core Git commands and systems, however, it is executed through icons and buttons instead of terminal commands . 
  * SourceTree is used as an alternative to the terminal when using Git .
